==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin [[multi]]
[[Category:Latin derivations]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈmʌltɪ/}}
*[[SAMPA]]: //

===Prefix===
[[Category:English prefixes]]
'''multi-'''

#Resembling, pertaining to [[many]] or many things.
# {{rfv-sense}} People of multi-racial and multi-ethnic heritage.  While other terms are also used, including "mixed" and "biracial," the term "multi" is widely considered the proper word, and it is also used by many academics.  An example of its usage: "Yes, she's multi; her father's white and her mother is Japanese and Korean."  This terminology is slowly achieving greater use, especially with the advent of a burgeoning multiracial student-driven movement in the United States. 
